[http://www.smallnetbuilder.com/wireless/wireless-reviews/32148-powercloud-systems-skydog-beta-reviewed Per '''SmallNetBuilder'''], this is the [http://www.kickstarter.com/projects/110098832/skydog-your-home-network-reinvented '''Skydog''' router]. Per the FCC internal photos, this device uses the following. *an '''Atheros''' AR1022-AL1A WiSoC (presumably. it appears to be the only AR1X22 device with a valid part number) *'''Winbond''' W9751G6KB-25 RAM (probably) *an '''EnGenius''' EMP7618 wireless module **with an '''Atheros''' AR9382-AL1A **probable 00:02:6F ('''Senao''') OUI *an '''Atheros''' GbE Switch (looks like it ''may'' be AR8327N, but the image quality is horrid) "7016A054301f V: 1.10" is silkscreened on the main board.
"7016A0540028" and "V-1.20" is silkscreened on the board under the shield. The default credentials in this entry are derived from the FCC manual.
